post_content:
"A rational approach would simply be to harness capitalism and put a global, uniform price on carbon, refunding the revenue with tax cuts that spur growth. Simple, easy. Make it go global with a border tax adjustment."

What is scary here is the total misunderstanding or denial of capitalism when the commenter says "harness capitalism and put..."

It has never occurred to most people, I think, that capitalism means that you stop putting harnesses on people. It mean free and unrestricted trade. It does not mean taxes, and price fixing. 

http://www.wsj.com/articles/the-unsettling-anti-science-certitude-on-global-warming-1438300982

post_content:
Nations are guided by thought leaders. Where have they lead us? Who are they? What are the leading thoughts? 

We are not guided by the masses. This is an excuse made by the thought leaders when their plans fail. 

The average man is not a thought leader. 

Most of us don't take the time to inspect the foundations of our thinking. Most of us don't take the time to examine the rules, codes and guidelines we live by. If you look around at the man on the street you are looking mostly at followers. Most of us are followers, and even among the leaders they are followers for most of their lives.
post_title: Thought Leaders

post_content:
A valuable account of the ideas behind the choices. 

The corruption comes from the source. Sarah chairs says the source is the tip, the head, the leader of State. 

But the corruption that flows out is the negation of individual allocation of scarce resources. 

Excellent explanation of American riots in reason as a basis for govt. Ch 11.

The author goes through a list of fixes that can be implemented, some of them good some bad, but all directed at reducing corruption, but the type of corruption she is talking about is not adequately defined. 

http://www.amazon.com/Thieves-State-Corruption-Threatens-Security/dp/0393239462

post_content: This is a problem faced by many vertically-integrated companies. They have to pay more for an inferior product from within their own organization than they would in an unrestricted market. The CSUF faculty are not necessarily ignorant or even negligent. It is the protected textbook market that is at fault and excludes the work done by other investigators, such as the non, conformist professor and his students. http://m.ocregister.com/articles/goode-689026-text-math.html

post_content:
About 15 years ago I became disgusted with socialism and statism and I began looking into free market capitalism. 

It was in the process of that study, over a period of years, that I found something that I never expected: my own life. 

Now I can explain why I should have expected to find it there, and moreover how everyone should expect to find their life in there. Not just everyone reading this, but every human that will ever exist within a society.
post_title: Separate market and state
